results.name: Number of ways of factoring n with 3 levels of parentheses.
comment: a(n) depends only on prime signature of n (cf. A025487). So a(24) = a(375) since 24=2^3*3 and 375=3*5^3 both have prime signature (3,1).
link: R. J. Mathar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1295
results.author: _Christian G. Bower_, Oct 15 1999.
